Building from git repository
----------------------------

After a checkout, you need to generate the configure script
and some extra automake files.  Do this by running::

    autoreconf --install

Configure Examples
------------------

Build for MPI::

    configure --enable-parallel=mpi --enable-logging CXX=mpic++ CXXFLAGS="-std=c++11 -Wall -g -O"

Single-threaded build::

    configure CXXFLAGS="-std=c++11 -Wall -g -O"

Defaults from original git checkout::

    configure --enable-parallel=mpi --enable-logging CXX=mpic++ CXXFLAGS="-std=gnu++0x -Wall -g -O -fPIC"  --enable-debug --enable-error-injection --enable-keep-preservation-files

USE THIS!!
    configure --enable-parallel=mpi --enable-logging CXX=mpic++ --enable-debug --enable-cd-test --enable-error-injection --enable-keep-preservation-files
Random
------

This perl fragment will identify most of the conditional compilation flags.

perl -ane 'print "$ARGV: $_" if /\s*#if/' *.h

To verify preprocessor symbols are defined, pass -Wundef

    configure CXXFLAGS="-std=c++11 -Wall -Wundef -g -O"


